    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/1350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-01T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >April 1, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. My 96, March 31, noon. Francisco Alves Dos Santos, a Director of the Banco
                    Commercial of the State of Sao Paulo, has been appointed today by President
                    Vargas Director of Exchange of the Bank of Brazil and will take over his new
                    office on Monday. He is well known <pb facs="0391" n="383" xml:id="pg_383"/> to
                    the Embassy and informed me confidentially that the new exchange policy would be
                    put into effect immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
